Another feature that we

00:01:41.886 --> 00:01:43.256 A:middle
announced last year, that is

00:01:43.256 --> 00:01:45.306 A:middle
even a greater option, is inline

00:01:45.306 --> 00:01:45.746 A:middle
setup.

00:01:46.946 --> 00:01:48.626 A:middle
Now, inline setup lets your

00:01:48.626 --> 00:01:50.666 A:middle
users with no cards set up one,

00:01:50.806 --> 00:01:52.576 A:middle
and then return to the purchase

00:01:52.806 --> 00:01:53.526 A:middle
in one step.

00:01:54.526 --> 00:01:56.276 A:middle
All you have to do is always

00:01:56.276 --> 00:01:58.236 A:middle
show the Apple Pay button if the

00:01:58.236 --> 00:01:59.176 A:middle
device supports it.

00:02:00.196 --> 00:02:02.116 A:middle
If the user has no cards, you

00:02:02.116 --> 00:02:03.386 A:middle
can use the Set Up with Apple

00:02:03.386 --> 00:02:05.576 A:middle
Pay button, shown here, to make

00:02:05.576 --> 00:02:06.836 A:middle
it even clearer to the user.

00:02:07.996 --> 00:02:08.826 A:middle
Now, when the user taps that

00:02:08.826 --> 00:02:10.846 A:middle
button, the setup flow is

00:02:10.846 --> 00:02:12.226 A:middle
presented inside of your app,

00:02:12.836 --> 00:02:14.996 A:middle
which reduces the risk of users

00:02:14.996 --> 00:02:16.186 A:middle
leaving your experience.

00:02:16.266 --> 00:02:17.686 A:middle
And, this is commonly known as

00:02:17.686 --> 00:02:18.306 A:middle
abandonment.

00:02:19.406 --> 00:02:20.896 A:middle
And, to support this, no

00:02:20.896 --> 00:02:21.916 A:middle
additional work is required from

00:02:21.916 --> 00:02:21.983 A:middle
you.

00:02:24.266 --> 00:02:25.666 A:middle
Once the card is set up, it

00:02:25.666 --> 00:02:27.056 A:middle
returns the user to the purchase

00:02:27.056 --> 00:02:27.606 A:middle
immediately.

00:02:28.566 --> 00:02:30.206 A:middle
We even automatically activate

00:02:30.206 --> 00:02:31.146 A:middle
the card via SMS.

00:02:32.376 --> 00:02:34.206 A:middle
Now, even with all of this, it's

00:02:34.206 --> 00:02:35.686 A:middle
still faster than manual entry.

00:02:36.386 --> 00:02:37.396 A:middle
And, you should adopt this in

00:02:37.396 --> 00:02:38.506 A:middle
your apps, if you haven't

00:02:38.506 --> 00:02:39.606 A:middle
already, for a great user

00:02:39.606 --> 00:02:40.196 A:middle
experience.

00:02:41.556 --> 00:02:42.876 A:middle
That's not the only feature we

00:02:42.876 --> 00:02:43.796 A:middle
announced in the last year.

00:02:44.396 --> 00:02:46.326 A:middle
To help with faster checkout, we

00:02:46.326 --> 00:02:47.716 A:middle
also introduced error handling,

00:02:47.716 --> 00:02:48.796 A:middle
and that's been great for

00:02:48.796 --> 00:02:49.266 A:middle
developers.

00:02:49.766 --> 00:02:53.006 A:middle
Error handling gives you control

00:02:53.006 --> 00:02:54.346 A:middle
over nonfatal errors in the

00:02:54.346 --> 00:02:55.046 A:middle
Apple Pay Sheet.

00:02:55.046 --> 00:02:57.386 A:middle
And, this allows you to provide

00:02:57.386 --> 00:02:58.806 A:middle
your own custom error messages

00:02:59.236 --> 00:03:00.906 A:middle
to the user for billing and

00:02:59.236 --> 00:03:00.906 A:middle
to the user for billing and

00:03:00.906 --> 00:03:01.626 A:middle
shipping issues.

00:03:02.346 --> 00:03:03.596 A:middle
And, that's so they can more

00:03:03.596 --> 00:03:05.256 A:middle
easily resolve those issues, and

00:03:05.256 --> 00:03:06.136 A:middle
get back to purchasing.

00:03:06.956 --> 00:03:08.286 A:middle
And, that's great for higher

00:03:08.286 --> 00:03:08.766 A:middle
conversion.

00:03:09.286 --> 00:03:11.176 A:middle
Now, some tips for error

00:03:11.226 --> 00:03:11.596 A:middle
handling.

00:03:12.496 --> 00:03:13.776 A:middle
One thing we want to make clear,

00:03:14.256 --> 00:03:16.096 A:middle
is that it's still important to

00:03:16.096 --> 00:03:17.296 A:middle
expect fuzzy data.

00:03:18.316 --> 00:03:19.826 A:middle
The user has one set of data in

00:03:19.826 --> 00:03:21.196 A:middle
Apple Pay, and that's shared

00:03:21.196 --> 00:03:23.136 A:middle
across many apps and websites.

00:03:23.736 --> 00:03:24.826 A:middle
And, we don't want the user--

00:03:24.826 --> 00:03:26.586 A:middle
don't want to force the user to

00:03:26.586 --> 00:03:27.836 A:middle
conform to everybody's

00:03:27.886 --> 00:03:29.616 A:middle
individual business logic, as

00:03:30.126 --> 00:03:31.066 A:middle
that requires the user to

00:03:31.066 --> 00:03:33.716 A:middle
reenter information, which just

00:03:33.716 --> 00:03:35.406 A:middle
increases friction, and will

00:03:35.406 --> 00:03:36.866 A:middle
reduce your overall conversion

00:03:36.866 --> 00:03:37.026 A:middle
rate.

00:03:38.056 --> 00:03:39.856 A:middle
Instead, you should do your best

00:03:39.906 --> 00:03:41.276 A:middle
to accept a range of inputs.

00:03:41.466 --> 00:03:43.416 A:middle
For example, Zip and Zip + 4.

00:03:44.666 --> 00:03:46.196 A:middle
And, infer what details you can

00:03:46.196 --> 00:03:48.066 A:middle
from other fields such as city

00:03:48.066 --> 00:03:49.036 A:middle
and state from Zip.

00:03:50.406 --> 00:03:52.016 A:middle
Now, that's not all the features

00:03:52.016 --> 00:03:52.566 A:middle
that we announced.

